The President begins his remarks by sending thoughts and prayers to Steve Scalise, who is in the hospital after being shot at a congressional baseball practice. He praises the bravery of the Capitol Police officers who saved lives during the shooting and thanks the first responders. The President then shifts to discussing the state of the economy, highlighting low unemployment rates and record levels of job and business enthusiasm. He mentions recent deals for military equipment and emphasizes the need for a well-trained workforce. He announces the signing of an executive order to expand apprenticeships and vocational training, aiming to help Americans find rewarding careers and support themselves and their families. The President is joined by apprentices and governors, as well as CEOs who support the apprenticeship initiatives. He emphasizes the importance of keeping jobs in America and training American workers. The President concludes by urging everyone to work together to restore the American Dream and address the drug problem in the country.